What other student organizations had a high 
profile during that time other than the Corps and

09:56.034 --> 10:01.259
the MSC? What about singing cadets? Singing 
cadets were very popular. They were still fairly

10:07.385 --> 10:12.311
early in their growth cycle. You may happen to know 
what year Bob Boone started. I don't know if it was

10:18.223 --> 10:21.450
59 or 60 or 61. It was fairly early. He was new and he 
was building and I don't know who his predecessor

10:24.397 --> 10:36.643
was or if he had a predecessor but it was building 
but it was still very impressive then we always

10:37.096 --> 10:39.218
enjoyed hearing them sing. What about Yale 
leaders? How much prestige did Yale leaders have?

10:43.762 --> 10:45.224
They had a lot. Probably, they were probably, 
because they were more visible, they probably had

10:45.324 --> 11:06.343
more prestige and influence than student body 
presidents or MSC council presidents or I think

10:45.324 --> 11:06.343
that because they were so visible at football 
games, they probably, I think they and the corps

10:45.324 --> 11:06.343
commanders in fact they probably even had more 
more visibility and prestige even than the corps

11:07.943 --> 11:34.963
commander did as far as uh because you know at the 
yell leader at the yell practices over in the grove

11:07.943 --> 11:34.963
and at the games themselves the head yell leader 
and the yell leaders were up you know that they were

11:07.943 --> 11:34.963
up rallying the troops and telling the fables and 
leading the yells and everything so with the the

11:07.943 --> 11:34.963
other folks you're more behind the scenes and 
don't have the the visibility or the publicity

11:35.399 --> 11:38.122
that the Yale leaders did. Did you know that secret 
fraternities existed? I did not. I have heard in

11:44.407 --> 11:47.870
subsequent years that some did. I was never 
invited to join one and actually was kind of

11:47.890 --> 12:03.685
revolted at the idea of secret fraternities 
because to me that smacks of elitism. For sure,

12:04.171 --> 12:13.667
maybe it's a way of networking and a way of 
maneuvering yourself and your buddies into

12:04.171 --> 12:13.667
positions of power and influence, but I don't like 
that. I prefer a meritocracy where people can, by

12:13.747 --> 12:30.094
their talent and their hustle and their 
leadership, I just think it's easier to sustain

12:13.747 --> 12:30.094
that, whereas if a secret cabal is holding you in 
place, and you're dependent more on them than you

12:31.492 --> 12:50.648
are on the facts and genuinely polling and leading 
public opinion to help you, you can maneuver

12:31.492 --> 12:50.648
yourself into some pretty untenable positions 
and then you either have to

12:51.995 --> 13:11.990
have your cabal artificially hold you in place or 
else you kind of go down in flames and disgrace with

12:51.995 --> 13:11.990
nobody supporting you publicly because if your 
cabal comes out to support you then they identify

12:51.995 --> 13:11.990
themselves and I just don't like that system and 
yet I kind of suspect some of that might still be

12:51.995 --> 13:11.990
going on. You did know about steam tunnels. Yep. 
Did you ever go down in the steam? Absolutely. When

13:18.018 --> 13:25.305
we were, again, my freshman year, when we were over 
in dorm seven, from the back of the dorm, you could

13:18.018 --> 13:25.305
see the band hall. And the band had abused us on one 
occasion. We had done very well that semester with

13:32.751 --> 13:44.682
some of the, well, the previous week had done well 
at a march off and had won it. and had beaten either

13:45.877 --> 13:50.062
one of their units or one of their favorites. And 
maybe there might have been some personal

13:51.323 --> 14:06.359
rivalries between some of our upperclassmen and 
some of them, but at any rate, during a march-off,

13:51.323 --> 14:06.359
there's a way you can do an offbeat roll-off 
between songs. The drummers will roll, and if they

14:08.161 --> 14:12.846
intend to do this, They'll roll and then start the 
next song one beat early which means that you're on

14:13.282 --> 14:20.819
the wrong foot as you come by. And they did that to us 
as we were approaching the reviewing stand. and as

14:26.765 --> 14:46.731
a result we had some guys you know we'd been told if 
that happens you just continue you don't do a

14:26.765 --> 14:46.731
change step you just continue and you shift to the 
right foot well some of the few of the guys didn't

14:26.765 --> 14:46.731
remember that or were confused and they were used 
to hitting the beat on the left foot so they changed

14:26.765 --> 14:46.731
step others didn't and so here we are out of sync as 
we go by the reviewing stand. So we get a bad grade

14:50.295 --> 14:52.779
that week. Well, we seethe and simmer about that a 
little bit and we decide we're going to flood the

14:52.980 --> 14:59.331
band dorm. And so we did some intelligence 
collection. We got in the steam tunnels. Earl

15:06.583 --> 15:10.710
Henderson and I again were, in fact Earl drew up the 
the ops plan the sequencing of events and the

15:10.825 --> 15:35.483
timing and everything and we did the recon 
ordering in there knowing where found in the steam

15:10.825 --> 15:35.483
tunnels most of the the valves the wheels on the 
valves had been removed so you just had the stem

15:10.825 --> 15:35.483
coming out with the little square thing on it but it 
was to prevent the tampering with it but we had

15:10.825 --> 15:35.483
found one and had stored it in our room And so we had a 
way to turn the main valve. So we knew then, once we

15:39.983 --> 15:47.113
had found that, we knew we could do it if the guys 
didn't get caught. So one day at noon, we had some

15:47.193 --> 16:04.018
fish dressed up as sophomores, and they were 
wearing their hats and wearing the slick black

15:47.193 --> 16:04.018
belt and the black braid so they could go in and 
disguise themselves. And in case anybody was left

16:04.235 --> 16:13.688
in the dorm, well, sure enough, there was a guy in 
the dorm and he didn't go to chow with them. and they

16:15.355 --> 16:43.658
said well we're up here we're looking for Fish 
Rabel or uh... uh... or uh... we're looking for

16:15.355 --> 16:43.658
Chip Rabel who was a sophomore this was a fish but it 
was from the same hometown from Spring Branch knew

16:15.355 --> 16:43.658
a name to drop and he said he said well you won't find 
him uh... he said he's at Chow and besides well he

16:15.355 --> 16:43.658
wouldn't why would you expect him to be here during 
Chow he said well we were supposed to meet him and

16:15.355 --> 16:43.658
uh... we're running late we thought he might have 
waited for us and so anyway the guy went on back into

16:15.355 --> 16:43.658
his room and then later on got a little bit 
suspicious, but by this time, that group

16:43.739 --> 16:51.612
retreated. We had a group going to every floor, 
every bathroom, taking the heads off of the flush

16:52.013 --> 17:04.414
toilets

16:52.013 --> 17:04.414
after the water was turned off. and they got those 
well that group didn't do theirs but the other see

17:04.462 --> 17:25.812
two four six we got seven out of eight of the 
bathrooms done I was in the steam tunnel with the

17:04.462 --> 17:25.812
wheel and as the last guy left on his way out of the 
building he gave the secret knock on the door and

17:04.462 --> 17:25.812
turned the valve and then beat feet back through 
and get to our dorm and then we're in that window

17:26.433 --> 17:39.919
looking out that back window to see what the 
reaction was and just as those guys were leaving

17:26.433 --> 17:39.919
the guy who had been contacted had second thoughts 
and he thought something's happening and he went

17:40.844 --> 18:03.628
out and as he was going out the door he was headed out 
the door to sound a warning when the flood started

17:40.844 --> 18:03.628
and so they they reacted pretty quickly because he 
ran right across there to the chow hall and then all

17:40.844 --> 18:03.628
the band people ran back so there was a good 
indo-chinese fire drill there i need to quit

